creator: Liberate
descriptionHtml:
Liberate is the #1 meditation app for the Black, Indigenous, and People of Color community. Listen to dozens of guided meditations to ease anxiety, find gratitude, heal internalized racism and micro-aggressions and celebrate Blackness. For us, by us. (249 - this is above fold)

Our content is carefully curated by leading meditation teachers of color that represent a broad range of experiences and lineages in the practice.

Liberate is a perfect place for beginners, and also includes content for intermediate and advanced users, too! Meditations are available from 5 – 25 minutes in length, so you can adjust your practice to whatever your heart is calling for.

Subscribe to Liberate Plus for a 7-day free trial to access the entire content library.

Enjoy meditations and talks that focus on:
Anxiety and Stress
Depression
Micro-aggressions
Internalized racism
Ancestral Healing
Grief and loss
Overcoming addiction
Interconnectedness
Forgiveness
Non-judgment
Sleep
Worry
Gratitude
Joy

Come sit with us.

SUBSCRIPTION PRICING AND TERMS
Liberate offers two auto-renewing subscription options:
$9.99 per month
$71.99 per year (that's just $5.99 a month)

Subscriptions renew automatically. To manage your subscription, go to your Google Play Store settings and turn off auto-renew. Your Google Play account will be charged after the 7-day free trial ends.

Please note: these prices are for United States customers only. Pricing in other countries can vary, depending on conversion rates and the local currency in your country of residence.

Our terms and conditions:
https://liberatemeditation.com/terms

Our privacy policy:
https://liberatemeditation.com/privacy
descriptionShort: Meditation For Black, Indigenous, and People of Color

title: Liberate

creator: Liberate
descriptionHtml:
Liberate is the meditation app for us, by us that is Black-owned. We’re not only just a meditation app, we’re a safe space for the Black community to develop a daily meditation habit. Anyone is welcome to use Liberate, we just want to be clear who we’re here for.


With popular meditations and talks like The Joy of Gratitude, Mindfulness of Healing, and For The Ancestor In You we offer a meditation journey that speaks to the realities of being Black in the modern day. Our carefully-curated library of over 260+ titles is led by teachers of color representing a wide range of experiences and lineages in their practice. Our focus areas include:


Anxiety and Stress

Depression

Microaggressions

Internalized Racism

Ancestral Healing

Grief and Loss

Overcoming Addiction

Interconnectedness

Forgiveness

Non-Judgment

Sleep

Worry

Gratitude

Joy


Liberate is the perfect place for those who want to develop a regular meditation practice or simply explore a new intention. Choose from meditations ranging from 5 to 25 minutes in length, which you can enjoy anytime, anywhere.


Get started with a limited selection of free content and one free preview of a premium Liberate Plus mediation. With a Plus subscription you get access to our full library of 260+ meditations and talks with the option to listen offline.


Come sit with us! All are welcome.


SUBSCRIPTION AND PRICING TERMS

Liberate offers two auto-renewing subscriptions at $9.99/month and $71.99/year (that's only $5.99/month). The subscription begins with a 7 day free trial at the end of which your card will be charged for your selected option. To manage your subscription or cancel, go to your iTunes Account Settings and turn off auto-renew.


These prices are for United States customers only. Pricing in other countries may vary depending on conversion rates and local currencies.


Read our terms and conditions: https://liberatemeditation.com/terms


Read our privacy policy: https://liberatemeditation.com/privacy

appDetails.recentChangesHtml: We've made some updates to the user experience to provide recommended meditations!

Liberate is the meditation app for us, by us that is Black-owned. We’re not only just a meditation app, we’re a safe space for the Black community to develop a daily meditation habit. Anyone is welcome to use Liberate, we just want to be clear who we’re here for.


With popular meditations and talks like The Joy of Gratitude, Mindfulness of Healing, and For The Ancestor In You we offer a meditation journey that speaks to the realities of being Black in the modern day. Our carefully-curated library of over 260+ titles is led by teachers of color representing a wide range of experiences and lineages in their practice. Our focus areas include:


Anxiety and Stress

Depression

Microaggressions

Internalized Racism

Ancestral Healing

Grief and Loss

Overcoming Addiction

Interconnectedness

Forgiveness

Non-Judgment

Sleep

Worry

Gratitude

Joy


Liberate is the perfect place for those who want to develop a regular meditation practice or simply explore a new intention. Choose from meditations ranging from 5 to 25 minutes in length, which you can enjoy anytime, anywhere.


Get started with a limited selection of free content and one free preview of a premium Liberate Plus mediation. With a Plus subscription you get access to our full library of 260+ meditations and talks with the option to listen offline.


Come sit with us! All are welcome.


SUBSCRIPTION AND PRICING TERMS

Liberate offers two auto-renewing subscriptions at $9.99/month and $71.99/year (that's only $5.99/month). The subscription begins with a 7 day free trial at the end of which your card will be charged for your selected option. To manage your subscription or cancel, go to your iTunes Account Settings and turn off auto-renew.


These prices are for United States customers only. Pricing in other countries may vary depending on conversion rates and local currencies.


Read our terms and conditions: https://liberatemeditation.com/terms


Read our privacy policy: https://liberatemeditation.com/privacy

title: Liberate

creator: LIBERATEVILLAGE.COM
descriptionHtml:
LIBERATEVILLAGE.COM is here to help us as the African Diaspora heal our emotional wounds so we can come together to organize.

We must come together to organize to protect our race, culture, and children.

This healing app contains meditations and music meant to help you get back into your body to release the trauma.

Get quiet and take some breaths and/or dance out the shame - whatever space you are in we welcome.

This app is meant for and designed for the Black community and African Diaspora.

We do not promote hate but we are RACE FIRST.

Join us also as we celebrate the birth of Marcus Garvey, the father of modern Pan-Africanism.

Blessings on your journey of healing!

Founder/Chief JULIO // HERU

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
We've made the following updates:
-We've fixed a bug where you did not have controls for the audio playing when the screen was locked.
- We've added a way for you to receive help right from Home. Tap the "?" and chat directly with HERU if you're experiencing a bug, have an idea, or just want to learn more about the app and vision. You can now delete your comment after you've posted one. We've made some slight changes so we're both on iOS & Android FOR UNITY!

title: LIBERATEVILLAGE.COM

creator: LIBERATEVILLAGE.COM
descriptionHtml:
THE VILLAGE! from LIBERATEVILLAGE.COM is here to help heal the relationship between Black men and women to restore the village.

The emotional wounds and trauma that we carry keep us divided and prevent intimacy within each other.

If we want to organize as a community and as an African Diaspora globally, we must develop deeper presence and empathy with each other.

Join us as begin a new chapter for our people.

Blessings on your journey of healing!
Founder/Chief JULIO // HERU

appDetails.recentChangesHtml: We've made updates to the branding shortening the name from LIBERATEVILLAGE.COM to THE VILLAGE! We've also updated the app icon and to reflect our focus which is to support the HEALING OF HEALTHY BLACK LOVE. We've also made some minor updates to make the app run smoother.

title: THE VILLAGE!
